{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Understanding linear regressions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 83,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
    "import statsmodels.formula.api as smf\n",
    "\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 84,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sns.set_context('poster')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate data\n",
    "\n",
    "We generate synthetic data using a form of structural equation modeling.\n",
    "This way, we can check whether we are able to recover the coefficients."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 94,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "N = 1000\n",
    "\n",
    "beta_g1 = 1.4\n",
    "beta_g2 = -.8\n",
    "\n",
    "mean_g1 = -2\n",
    "mean_g2 = 10"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 95,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "A = np.random.normal(size=N * 2)\n",
    "B = np.r_[\n",
    "    beta_g1 * A[:int(len(A)/2)] + np.random.normal(mean_g1, size=N),\n",
    "    beta_g2 * A[int(len(A)/2):] + np.random.normal(mean_g2, size=N)\n",
    "]\n",
    "group = [1] * N + [2] * N"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 96,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<div>\n",
       "<style scoped>\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n",
       "        vertical-align: middle;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n",
       "        vertical-align: top;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe thead th {\n",
       "        text-align: right;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "</style>\n",
       "<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n",
       "  <thead>\n",
       "    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n",
       "      <th></th>\n",
       "      <th>A</th>\n",
       "      <th>B</th>\n",
       "      <th>group</th>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "  </thead>\n",
       "  <tbody>\n",
       "    <tr>\n",
       "      <th>0</th>\n",
       "      <td>0.496714</td>\n",
       "      <td>-1.979778</td>\n",
       "      <td>1</td>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "    <tr>\n",
       "      <th>1</th>\n",
       "      <td>-0.138264</td>\n",
       "      <td>-2.338089</td>\n",
       "      <td>1</td>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "    <tr>\n",
       "      <th>2</th>\n",
       "      <td>0.647689</td>\n",
       "      <td>-1.885656</td>\n",
       "      <td>1</td>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "    <tr>\n",
       "      <th>3</th>\n",
       "      <td>1.523030</td>\n",
       "      <td>-0.175720</td>\n",
       "      <td>1</td>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "    <tr>\n",
       "      <th>4</th>\n",
       "      <td>-0.234153</td>\n",
       "      <td>-4.221429</td>\n",
       "      <td>1</td>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "  </tbody>\n",
       "</table>\n",
       "</div>"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "          A         B group\n",
       "0  0.496714 -1.979778     1\n",
       "1 -0.138264 -2.338089     1\n",
       "2  0.647689 -1.885656     1\n",
       "3  1.523030 -0.175720     1\n",
       "4 -0.234153 -4.221429     1"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 96,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'A': A,\n",
    "    'B': B,\n",
    "    'group': group\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "df['group'] = df['group'].astype('category')\n",
    "\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Fit model\n",
    "\n",
    "The model:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Y = \\beta_0 + \\beta_1 \\cdot group + \\beta_2 \\cdot A + \\beta_3 \\cdot A \\cdot group + \\epsilon\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 97,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mod = sm.formula.ols(formula='B ~ A * group', data=df)\n",
    "fit = mod.fit()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Investigate result"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Retrieve coefficients"
   ]

    "res = fit.summary()\n",

   "source": [
    "coefs = pd.read_html(res.tables[1].as_html(), header=0, index_col=0)[0].loc[:, 'coef']\n",

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Understand"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 100,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fitted_beta_g1 = coefs['A']\n",
    "fitted_beta_g2 = coefs['A'] + coefs['A:group[T.2]']\n",
    "\n",
    "fitted_mean_g1 = coefs['Intercept']\n",
    "fitted_mean_g2 = coefs['Intercept'] + coefs['group[T.2]']"
   ]

   "source": [
    "def annotate_plot(space, mean, beta, color):\n",
    "    ax.plot(space, mean + beta * space, color=color)\n",
    "    ax.axhline(mean, ls='dashed', color=color)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
    "ax = sns.scatterplot(x='A', y='B', hue='group', data=df, s=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "sub = df.loc[df['group'] == 1, 'A']\n",
    "annotate_plot(np.linspace(sub.min(), sub.max()), fitted_mean_g1, fitted_beta_g1, sns.color_palette()[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "sub = df.loc[df['group'] == 2, 'A']\n",
    "annotate_plot(np.linspace(sub.min(), sub.max()), fitted_mean_g2, fitted_beta_g2, sns.color_palette()[1])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.5), loc='center left', frameon=False)"
   ]
